  {title: "Magnum Opus", episode_number: "S8, Ep13", description: "\nWhile Reid copes with a loss in his personal life, the rest of the BAU travels to San Francisco to investigate victims discovered in the Mission District.    ", season_id: 2485, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2013-01-23", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2550578/?ref_=ttep_ep13"},
  {title: "All That Remains", episode_number: "S8, Ep14", description: "\nWhen the daughters of Bruce Morrison, a writer whose wife mysteriously vanished a year ago, go missing on the anniversary of their mother's disappearance, the BAU is brought in to study Morrison as a possible suspect.    ", season_id: 2485, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2013-02-06", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2547282/?ref_=ttep_ep14"},
  {title: "Broken", episode_number: "S8, Ep15", description: "\nThe BAU heads to Austin to investigate victims found there with their watches set inaccurately, a clue which may connect the crimes.    ", season_id: 2485, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2013-02-20", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2691222/?ref_=ttep_ep15"},
  {title: "Carbon Copy", episode_number: "S8, Ep16", description: "\nWhen victims are found in Philadelphia in a similar style to victims of The Replicator, the stalker who has been tracking the BAU's every move, the team thinks this could be the break they need to try and apprehend him.    ", season_id: 2485, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2013-02-27", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2689294/?ref_=ttep_ep16"},
  {title: "The Gathering", episode_number: "S8, Ep17", description: "\nThe BAU investigates victims who were documenting their personal lives and inner desires on blog posts and social media. Also, Kevin gets jealous when he learns Garcia may have a new love interest.    ", season_id: 2485, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2013-03-20", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2700928/?ref_=ttep_ep17"},
  {title: "Restoration", episode_number: "S8, Ep18", description: "\nThe BAU goes to Morgan's old neighbourhood in urban Chicago in search of an UnSub targeting middle-aged men, and a clue leads Morgan to believe that they are after someone connected to the man who molested him as a child.    ", season_id: 2485, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2013-04-03", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2713424/?ref_=ttep_ep18"},
  {title: "Pay It Forward", episode_number: "S8, Ep19", description: "\nWhen a time capsule in a small Colorado town is opened 25 years later and contains a gruesome discovery, the BAU investigates that crime and a possible link to the death of a local police officer.    ", season_id: 2485, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2013-04-10", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2757554/?ref_=ttep_ep19"},
  {title: "Alchemy", episode_number: "S8, Ep20", description: "\nThe BAU travel to Rapid City after two male victims are discovered murdered in a ritualistic manner. Also, Reid continues to grieve over Maeve's death.    ", season_id: 2485, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2013-05-01", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2757558/?ref_=ttep_ep20"},
  {title: "Nanny Dearest", episode_number: "S8, Ep21", description: "\nThe BAU travels to Los Angeles looking for an UnSub who is kidnapping nannies and the children they care for on the same day each year.    ", season_id: 2485, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2013-05-08", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2757556/?ref_=ttep_ep21"},
  {title: "#6", episode_number: "S8, Ep22", description: "\nThe BAU heads to Detroit when couples are murdered and put in their cars. Meanwhile, Blake's husband shares news with her.    ", season_id: 2485, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2013-05-15", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2757560/?ref_=ttep_ep22"},
  {title: "Brothers Hotchner", episode_number: "S8, Ep23", description: "\nHotch receives a telephone call from his estranged New York based brother Sean, who he has not heard from in four years and coincidentally while Hotch and Jack are in New York visiting Beth. Now working as a bartender in a club, Sean wants Hotch's help in a death that occurred in the club, where the woman in question quickly bled out through her eyes, mouth and nose just before her death. Hotch convinces the team that this death is the basis for a case when Sean tells him that his own girlfriend also recently died the same way. The team quickly learns that these two ...    ", season_id: 2485, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2013-05-22", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2757562/?ref_=ttep_ep23"},
  {title: "The Replicator", episode_number: "S8, Ep24", description: "\nImmediately following the Ecstacy case in New York City, the Replicator has hacked into Garcia's computer system, on which he posts photographs of each of the team members in New York and his \"Zugzwang\" calling card. Although he has taunted most of the team members individually in the past, he seems to focus his attention on one team member while in New York. That focus, another calling card left by the Replicator in what he believes is from a past case, and that he seems to have easy access to almost anywhere the team has access, leads to the team believing he works ...    ", season_id: 2485, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2013-05-22", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2853128/?ref_=ttep_ep24"},
  {title: "It Takes a Village", episode_number: "S7, Ep1", description: "\nIt's been seven months since Prentiss' death, and three months since JJ returned to the unit to fill Prentiss' empty position. Ever since Prentiss' death, Morgan had been working to find and capture Prentiss' murderer, Ian Doyle, first unsanctioned but then within the scope of the team but still without any government authority. It is because of that unsanctioned nature that the team members individually are appearing at a senate committee hearing into the case, which led to the death of two agents. Morgan felt the best way to locate Doyle was to locate his son, ...    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2011-09-21", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1974554/?ref_=ttep_ep1"},
  {title: "Proof", episode_number: "S7, Ep2", description: "\nThe team travels to Durant, Oklahoma, where two females - both low risk in their late teens, long blond hair and blue eyes - were found sexually assaulted then murdered within a three day span. Other similarities between the two murders are that the body dump sites are public, the victims were not wearing their own clothes but rather 1980's vintage clothing, and that the killer used sulfuric acid to blind the victims. From this evidence, the team believes the unsub is homeless, and is using the acid as a measure of power. They also know that the victims are surrogates...    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2011-09-28", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1990405/?ref_=ttep_ep2"},
  {title: "Dorado Falls", episode_number: "S7, Ep3", description: "\nThe BAU investigate a mass murder at Synalock, an Internet security company located in Charlottesville, Virginia. Five people were shot, while three others were stabbed. By the severity of the killings, the company's CEO, Adam Werner, was the supposed intended target. They also surmise that despite the different styles of killings, there is only one unsub. When Mark and Mary Dolan are later that day found shot to death in their home, the BAU tie the two sets of murders together, the connection being the Dolan's son, Luke Dolan, who the BAU are certain is the unsub. ...    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2011-10-05", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1995609/?ref_=ttep_ep3"},
  {title: "Painless", episode_number: "S7, Ep4", description: "\nTen years ago, Hotch and Rossi, as part of the BAU at the time, worked on a mass murder case in Boise, Idaho, where bright and well liked but narcissistic North Valley High School student Randy Slade killed thirteen of his classmates in a lunch hour shooting and cell phone detonated bombing in the school's cafeteria. He himself was also killed. As several of the survivors return to Boise to commemorate the ten year anniversary of the massacre, a copycat killer seems to be on the loose. The local authorities and media believe that Randy's then seven year old brother, ...    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2011-10-12", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2009816/?ref_=ttep_ep4"},
  {title: "From Childhood's Hour", episode_number: "S7, Ep5", description: "\nThe BAU team investigates the abductions of young children with troubled mothers in St. Louis. Also, Rossi reconnects with his first wife who has shocking news for him.    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2011-10-19", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2030847/?ref_=ttep_ep5"},
  {title: "Epilogue", episode_number: "S7, Ep6", description: "\nThe BAU search California's Angeles National Forest after a number of bodies mysteriously turn up in the mountain lakes there. Also, Rossi struggles with an agonizing decision regarding his ex-wife.    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2011-11-02", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2072418/?ref_=ttep_ep6"},
  {title: "There's No Place Like Home", episode_number: "S7, Ep7", description: "\nWhen a series of tornadoes hits Kansas, the BAU is called in to investigate bodies of young boys that turn up in the aftermath of the storms. Also, work pressures cause tension on JJ's home front.    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2011-11-09", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2072419/?ref_=ttep_ep7"},
  {title: "Hope", episode_number: "S7, Ep8", description: "\nGarcia leading a victims' support group is a measure to deal with the guilt associated with the death of her parents when she was a teenager, they who were looking for her past curfew late one evening when they were struck by a drunk driver. One of her closest friends in the group, Monica Kingston, just hit the seven year anniversary of the abduction of her then adolescent daughter Hope, who she believes is still alive. After the latest meeting, Garcia, who had just spoken to Monica, finds Monica's car left in the parking lot with the keys in the ignition and her ...    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2011-11-16", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2078889/?ref_=ttep_ep8"},
  {title: "Self Fulfilling Prophecy", episode_number: "S7, Ep9", description: "\nThe BAU team looks into the real reasons behind an apparent mass suicide of a small group of youths at a military academy. Also, Hotch and Morgan butt heads when a team member could be in jeopardy.    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2011-12-07", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2078078/?ref_=ttep_ep9"},
  {title: "The Bittersweet Science", episode_number: "S7, Ep10", description: "\nThe BAU team investigates a string of brutal bludgeonings in Philadelphia and is led to the city's boxing scene in search of the killer. Also, Hotch makes a connection with an attractive runner as they both train for a triathlon.    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2011-12-14", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2090786/?ref_=ttep_ep10"},
  {title: "True Genius", episode_number: "S7, Ep11", description: "\nThe BAU is called to San Francisco to investigate a possible Zodiac Killer copycat. Meanwhile, Reid wonders what he's done in his life as he reaches 30.    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2012-01-18", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2101639/?ref_=ttep_ep11"},
  {title: "Unknown Subject", episode_number: "S7, Ep12", description: "\nThe BAU is called to Houston, Texas when a past masked serial rapist coined the Piano Man - so named because of the piano wire he used to bind his victims - starts to re-offend, with his targets being his past victims. His crimes have since evolved where one of the victims, Vanessa Campbell, is abducted from her home - something the unsub had never done before - which they believe is meant to show his victims that they are safe nowhere from his clutches. He used drugs mimicking a date rape drug to knock the victims unconscious before committing his rapes. With news of...    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2012-01-25", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2117102/?ref_=ttep_ep12"},
  {title: "Snake Eyes", episode_number: "S7, Ep13", description: "\nEarly on a Sunday morning, a just woken up and extremely hung over Garcia is lamenting the fact of the huge argument she and Kevin had the previous night. Not one to face confrontation head on, she is not looking forward to her first post-fight talk with Kevin, which will happen sooner than later as she can hear that he will soon be finished his shower. That talk will be complicated by the person knocking on her front door. Meanwhile, the team is called to Atlantic City, New Jersey, where Danny Savino, a casino floor manager, was found dead in his office by a severe ...    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2012-02-08", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2128996/?ref_=ttep_ep13"},
  {title: "Closing Time", episode_number: "S7, Ep14", description: "\nThe BAU team hit choppy waters on the beaches of Southern California when they discover a series of bodies hidden in lifeguard towers along the coast.    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2012-02-15", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2128995/?ref_=ttep_ep14"},
  {title: "A Thin Line", episode_number: "S7, Ep15", description: "\nThe BAU team investigates a series of brutal home invasions and murders in California's Inland Empire that appear to be gang-related, but their investigation may uncover a more sinister motivation.    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2012-02-22", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2174385/?ref_=ttep_ep15"},
  {title: "A Family Affair", episode_number: "S7, Ep16", description: "\nThe BAU heads to Atlanta, where stabbings of prostitutes lead the team to suspect more than one unsub.    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2012-02-29", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2180877/?ref_=ttep_ep16"},
  {title: "I Love You, Tommy Brown", episode_number: "S7, Ep17", description: "\nWhen married couples fostering young children end up being killed in Seattle, the BAU team looks for an unsub with a maternal-yet-murderous instinct. Also, Garcia fears a possible proposition from Kevin.    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2012-03-14", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2281773/?ref_=ttep_ep17"},
  {title: "Foundation", episode_number: "S7, Ep18", description: "\nA boy named Angel is found wandering in the desert, and when another boy turns up missing, the BAU searches for the kidnapper.    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2012-04-04", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2309133/?ref_=ttep_ep18"},
  {title: "Heathridge Manor", episode_number: "S7, Ep19", description: "\nWhen an Oregon woman is found dead in an abandoned asylum, the BAU realizes that the victim is part of a series of gothic, ritualistic murders and the suspect might be a Satanist.    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2012-04-04", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2342615/?ref_=ttep_ep19"},
  {title: "The Company", episode_number: "S7, Ep20", description: "\nThe BAU searches for Morgan's cousin in Chicago when his sister Desiree is injured in a car accident after chasing a car presumed to be carrying his cousin.    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2012-04-11", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2299901/?ref_=ttep_ep20"},
  {title: "Divining Rod", episode_number: "S7, Ep21", description: "\nMoments after serial killer Rod Garrett is executed by firing squad at Gunter State Prison, another person kills in Enid, Oklahoma where the prison is located. The victimology and M.O. are the same as in Garrett's killings - female, young, blonde, pretty, and killed with a single stab through the heart using an ice pick. By the time the BAU arrive on the scene hours later, the unsub has killed a second victim - same victimology, same M.O. Garrett is survived by his wife, Helen Garrett, who stood by her husband's side through his incarceration, since he stood by her ...    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2012-05-02", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2336719/?ref_=ttep_ep21"},
  {title: "Profiling 101", episode_number: "S7, Ep22", description: "\nAs a favor owed, Rossi presents a lecture to a university undergraduate class, the lecture at which the entire team participates to support their respected colleague. Their presentation, which provides the basics of profiling, uses one of their cases as its centerpiece. The case, which so far spans twenty years since 1992, is of perhaps the most prolific serial killer they have ever tracked, he who killed up and down the west coast of the United States. The presentation makes the team not only reminisce about the case itself, but how the current team members first met...    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2012-05-09", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2366767/?ref_=ttep_ep22"},
  {title: "Hit", episode_number: "S7, Ep23", description: "\nIt's a lazy Saturday morning, a day off for the BAU. Beth has come over to Hotch's house to spend the day with him and Jack. JJ is playing with Henry while Will goes off to work. Morgan is going through Prentiss' just purchased house with her, the purchase pending the inspection which she seems to want to go badly as she seems to have buyer's remorse. Reid is Garcia's unofficial date to a sci-fi convention since she and Kevin split over his planned marriage proposal. And Rossi is heading home to bed after an all night cigar aficionado event... or so he says to Garcia ...    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2012-05-16", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2336721/?ref_=ttep_ep23"},
  {title: "Run", episode_number: "S7, Ep24", description: "\nOne of the diverse recruits -- the best and the brightest -- who arrive at the FBI Quantico Base for training is suspected of masterminding a terrorist attack.    ", season_id: 2486, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2015-09-27", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt2336723/?ref_=ttep_ep24"},
  {title: "The Longest Night", episode_number: "S6, Ep1", description: "\nAs The Prince of Darkness continues his murderous rampage across California, the BAU go after him to save Detective Spicer's daughter from him.    ", season_id: 2487, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-09-22", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1692557/?ref_=ttep_ep1"},
  {title: "JJ", episode_number: "S6, Ep2", description: "\nWhile trying to get two suspects to reveal what they've done with a missing woman, the BAU brace themselves for the loss of one of their own.    ", season_id: 2487, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-09-29", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1701258/?ref_=ttep_ep2"},
  {title: "Remembrance of Things Past", episode_number: "S6, Ep3", description: "\nWhen several women are found murdered in a similar fashion, Rossi revisits a case that has haunted him for 25 years.    ", season_id: 2487, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-10-06", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1716861/?ref_=ttep_ep3"},
  {title: "Compromising Positions", episode_number: "S6, Ep4", description: "\nThe BAU travel to Akron, Ohio, where two sets of married couples have been murdered in the span of a week. The husbands, who had Viagra in their system but who were not prescribed the drug, were shot while the wives were stabbed. The couples were forced to have sex with the husband wearing a condom, before they were killed. In reviewing the crime scenes, Morgan and Prentiss determine that the unsub is not a sexual sadist as he was trying to set a romantic mood for the kills, and is compensating for a probable recent bout of impotence. In interviewing the victims' ...    ", season_id: 2487, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-10-13", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1701257/?ref_=ttep_ep4"},
  {title: "Safe Haven", episode_number: "S6, Ep5", description: "\nThe BAU team is on the trail of a serial killer targeting families throughout the Midwest. Meanwhile, Morgan is concerned when Ellie runs away from her foster family and pays him a visit.    ", season_id: 2487, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-10-20", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1736078/?ref_=ttep_ep5"},
  {title: "Devil's Night", episode_number: "S6, Ep6", description: "\nJohn receives an invitation to attend an exclusive Devil's Night Soiree. Alex tries to diagnose Holden's strange condition.    ", season_id: 2487, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2015-10-28", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1736079/?ref_=ttep_ep6"},
  {title: "Middle Man", episode_number: "S6, Ep7", description: "\nWhen bodies begin turning up in the cornfields of Indiana, the team must catch a pack of serial killers targeting exotic dancers.    ", season_id: 2487, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-11-03", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1735538/?ref_=ttep_ep7"},
  {title: "Reflection of Desire", episode_number: "S6, Ep8", description: "\nThe team hunts a serial killer after a kidnapped woman is found murdered in an alley with her lips cut off.    ", season_id: 2487, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-11-10", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1738476/?ref_=ttep_ep8"},
  {title: "Into the Woods", episode_number: "S6, Ep9", description: "\nWhen a boy is found murdered on the Appalachian Trail, the BAU team goes deep into its forests in search of a man lurking in the wilderness who is targeting children.    ", season_id: 2487, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-11-17", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1755124/?ref_=ttep_ep9"},
  {title: "What Happens at Home...", episode_number: "S6, Ep10", description: "\nThe team searches a gated community for a killer who has strangled several women.    ", season_id: 2487, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-12-08", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1749100/?ref_=ttep_ep10"},
  {title: "25 to Life", episode_number: "S6, Ep11", description: "\nMorgan regrets his decision that a prisoner is ready for parole when the man murders someone days after being released.    ", season_id: 2487, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-12-15", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1782632/?ref_=ttep_ep11"},
  {title: "Corazon", episode_number: "S6, Ep12", description: "\nWhile the BAU are in Miami investigating a series of bizarre ritualistic murders, Reid suffers from intense migraines which makes him concerned about his health.    ", season_id: 2487, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2011-01-19", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1782633/?ref_=ttep_ep12"},
  {title: "The Thirteenth Step", episode_number: "S6, Ep13", description: "\nWhile the BAU chases a pair of young lovers on an interstate killing spree, Prentiss is contacted by an old friend with some bad news.    ", season_id: 2487, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2011-01-26", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1782019/?ref_=ttep_ep13"},
  {title: "Sense Memory", episode_number: "S6, Ep14", description: "\nThe BAU travels to Los Angeles to investigate unusual murders throughout the city. Also, more of Prentiss' mysterious past comes to light.    ", season_id: 2487, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2011-02-09", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1792213/?ref_=ttep_ep14"},
  {title: "Today I Do", episode_number: "S6, Ep15", description: "\nThe team travels to upstate New York to investigate a series of mysterious disappearances.    ", season_id: 2487, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2011-02-16", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1820833/?ref_=ttep_ep15"},
