  {title: "The Uncanny Valley", episode_number: "S5, Ep12", description: "\nAn unusual personal obsession is at the center of a BAU abduction case. Meanwhile, Hotch struggles with his return to work.    ", season_id: 2488, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-01-13", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1560814/?ref_=ttep_ep12"},
  {title: "Risky Business", episode_number: "S5, Ep13", description: "\nA rash of startling teen suicides in a small Wyoming town is the focus of a BAU investigation.    ", season_id: 2488, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-01-20", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1560564/?ref_=ttep_ep13"},
  {title: "Parasite", episode_number: "S5, Ep14", description: "\nThe BAU follows the mental decline of a con artist whose schemes have become so complicated that he begins to eliminate the people involved in them.    ", season_id: 2488, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-02-03", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1583441/?ref_=ttep_ep14"},
  {title: "Public Enemy", episode_number: "S5, Ep15", description: "\nThe BAU are called to Providence, Rhode Island where a serial killer is on the loose. He has killed three people thus far, each in an increasingly public location. Each victim was slashed across the throat with a knife, which is left at the scene without fingerprints. As the BAU go through the three murders thus far, they determine that the unsub is more like an arsonist than a killer in the way he approaches his crimes. The victims themselves seem to be secondary to the location for the unsub, and he is only killing when it is convenient as opposed to choosing a ...    ", season_id: 2488, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-02-10", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1591777/?ref_=ttep_ep15"},
  {title: "Mosley Lane", episode_number: "S5, Ep16", description: "\nThe BAU profiles a child abductor who may have been keeping children for more than eight years.    ", season_id: 2488, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-03-03", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1592610/?ref_=ttep_ep16"},
  {title: "Solitary Man", episode_number: "S5, Ep17", description: "\nThe Highway Serial Killer Database exists so that information can be collated for serial murders that would not otherwise be connected due to different police jurisdictions. In reviewing the database, the BAU determine that a serial killer has killed five women thus far, the bodies found hundreds of miles apart. However Reid determines that there is a geographical focus on Edgewood, New Mexico. Each woman was strangled, the bodies laid in a fetal position found in a public location such as a ditch, and there is no sexual assault. The BAU determine that the unsub is a ...    ", season_id: 2488, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-03-10", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1591778/?ref_=ttep_ep17"},
  {title: "The Fight", episode_number: "S5, Ep18", description: "\nThe BAU team travels to San Francisco to investigate the murders of several homeless men and teams up with a separate group of BAU operatives who are working another case they think is connected.    ", season_id: 2488, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-04-07", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1619514/?ref_=ttep_ep18"},
  {title: "Rite of Passage", episode_number: "S5, Ep19", description: "\nThe BAU team heads to Texas to track a serial killer targeting illegal immigrants attempting to make safe passage into the U.S..    ", season_id: 2488, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-04-14", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1624257/?ref_=ttep_ep19"},
  {title: "...A Thousand Words", episode_number: "S5, Ep20", description: "\nThe BAU team must profile a serial killer covered in tattoos who commits suicide, but leaves clues to the whereabouts of his last victim.    ", season_id: 2488, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-05-05", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1624560/?ref_=ttep_ep20"},
  {title: "Exit Wounds", episode_number: "S5, Ep21", description: "\nThe team, including Garcia, go to the small town of Franklin, Alaska to catch a rapidly escalating serial killer before the locals take justice into their own hands.    ", season_id: 2488, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-05-12", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1624256/?ref_=ttep_ep21"},
  {title: "The Internet Is Forever", episode_number: "S5, Ep22", description: "\nA serial killer in Boise, Idaho is revealed to have been posting his murders on the Internet, accumulating quite a collection of fans in the process.    ", season_id: 2488, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-05-19", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1647502/?ref_=ttep_ep22"},
  {title: "Our Darkest Hour", episode_number: "S5, Ep23", description: "\nThe BAU are called to California when a sadistic serial killer appears and begins killing people in the dark during the rolling blackouts.    ", season_id: 2488, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-05-26", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1647025/?ref_=ttep_ep23"},
  {title: "Mayhem", episode_number: "S4, Ep1", description: "\nAs the city is on high alert, the team begins to believe that they have made a mistake with the profile and that everything the terrorists have done so far may in fact just have been diversion for something even bigger.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2008-09-24", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256601/?ref_=ttep_ep1"},
  {title: "The Angel Maker", episode_number: "S4, Ep2", description: "\nOn the anniversary of a serial killer's execution, a murder spree which appears to be connected to him begins and the team must try and understand his mind in order to stop it.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2008-10-01", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256096/?ref_=ttep_ep2"},
  {title: "Minimal Loss", episode_number: "S4, Ep3", description: "\nReid and Prentiss, having gone undercover into an underground cult to investigate child abuse, get trapped inside the compound when a federal raid on it goes bad.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2008-10-08", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256100/?ref_=ttep_ep3"},
  {title: "Paradise", episode_number: "S4, Ep4", description: "\nA serial killer targeting couples stages their bodies in a way to make their deaths look like car accidents.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2008-10-22", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256101/?ref_=ttep_ep4"},
  {title: "Catching Out", episode_number: "S4, Ep5", description: "\nA man is jumping trains along Highway 99, brutally killing couples in their homes whenever he stops.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2008-10-29", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256102/?ref_=ttep_ep5"},
  {title: "The Instincts", episode_number: "S4, Ep6", description: "\nA child abduction case in Las Vegas causes Reid to have strange nightmares which appear to be connected to an event in his past.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2008-11-05", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256103/?ref_=ttep_ep6"},
  {title: "Memoriam", episode_number: "S4, Ep7", description: "\nDriven by his nightmares, Reid stays behind in Las Vegas to find his father in order to find out the truth about Riley Jenkins' murder.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2008-11-12", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256104/?ref_=ttep_ep7"},
  {title: "Masterpiece", episode_number: "S4, Ep8", description: "\nA serial killer turns himself in and challenges the team to find five people he has hidden somewhere before they die.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2008-11-19", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256105/?ref_=ttep_ep8"},
  {title: "52 Pickup", episode_number: "S4, Ep9", description: "\nA greatly sadistic serial killer who disembowels women and forces them to clean it up before killing them proves difficult to catch thanks to his social charm and simple, yet clever, disguises.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2008-11-26", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256106/?ref_=ttep_ep9"},
  {title: "Brothers in Arms", episode_number: "S4, Ep10", description: "\nMorgan, an ex-cop, takes it personally when a serial killer targets police officers in Phoenix, Arizona.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2008-12-10", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256086/?ref_=ttep_ep10"},
  {title: "Normal", episode_number: "S4, Ep11", description: "\nJess invites Russell to stay overnight at her place and is worried about how the guys will react. Winston gets a job at a radio station but finds it is not what he thought it would be. Nick pitches one of his marketing ideas to Russell.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2012-04-10", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256087/?ref_=ttep_ep11"},
  {title: "Soul Mates", episode_number: "S4, Ep12", description: "\nThe team suspects that a member of an affluent community is responsible for the disappearance of a young woman.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2009-01-14", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256088/?ref_=ttep_ep12"},
  {title: "Bloodline", episode_number: "S4, Ep13", description: "\nA family consisting of two parents and their son break into a home, kill the parents and kidnap their daughter. As the investigation proceeds, the BAU team begin to suspect that what they're dealing with is bigger than they thought.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2009-01-21", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256089/?ref_=ttep_ep13"},
  {title: "Cold Comfort", episode_number: "S4, Ep14", description: "\nA serial killer in the Olympia, Washington area has abducted four blonde, twenty-something women. When the third victim is found embalmed, the BAU are called in and suspect that the embalming is a way for him to spend more time with them.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2009-02-11", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256090/?ref_=ttep_ep14"},
  {title: "Zoe's Reprise", episode_number: "S4, Ep15", description: "\nA copycat serial killer is recreating murder techniques used by famous killers from the past.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2009-02-18", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256091/?ref_=ttep_ep15"},
  {title: "Pleasure Is My Business", episode_number: "S4, Ep16", description: "\nA high priced call girl that is killing her clients must be found and stopped.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2009-02-25", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256092/?ref_=ttep_ep16"},
  {title: "Demonology", episode_number: "S4, Ep17", description: "\nPrentiss learns from an old friend, John Cooley, that their mutual friend, Matthew Benton, just died from a heart attack. Prentiss had not seen either man in several years, both for different reasons. John also mentions that Matthew thought he was going to be killed just like \"T. Valentine\". In searching, Garcia does find someone matching that name in the area who recently died from dehydration. There are similarities between the two deaths but no medical rationale for tying the two together as murders. A third person in the area then dies in a similar way but again ...    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2009-03-11", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256093/?ref_=ttep_ep17"},
  {title: "Omnivore", episode_number: "S4, Ep18", description: "\nAfter being inactive for 10 years, Hotch's first BAU case, an elusive serial killer known as the Reaper, starts killing again.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2009-03-18", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256094/?ref_=ttep_ep18"},
  {title: "House on Fire", episode_number: "S4, Ep19", description: "\nWhen the kill count of a mass-murdering arsonist active in a small town reaches 31, the BAU are called in.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2009-03-25", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256095/?ref_=ttep_ep19"},
  {title: "Conflicted", episode_number: "S4, Ep20", description: "\nMale college students on spring break are being raped and murdered, presumably by a man and a woman working together. The BAU are called in and suspect a shy hotel cleaner and a receptionist.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2009-04-08", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256097/?ref_=ttep_ep20"},
  {title: "A Shade of Gray", episode_number: "S4, Ep21", description: "\nAn AMBER alert is activated for a young boy in Cherry Hill, New Jersey and the BAU suspect it to be the work of a pedophile who has abducted and killed two other boys.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2009-04-22", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256098/?ref_=ttep_ep21"},
  {title: "The Big Wheel", episode_number: "S4, Ep22", description: "\nThe team tracks down a highly obsessive-compulsive killer who targets blonde women and leaves messages to the police asking them to stop him.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2009-04-29", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1256099/?ref_=ttep_ep22"},
  {title: "Roadkill", episode_number: "S4, Ep23", description: "\nA serial killer in Bend, Oregon is deliberately killing people by running them over with his car.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2009-05-06", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1410492/?ref_=ttep_ep23"},
  {title: "Amplification", episode_number: "S4, Ep24", description: "\nThe BAU co-work with the U.S. Army to find the perpetrator behind an anthrax attack on a park in Annapolis, Maryland.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2009-05-13", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1425504/?ref_=ttep_ep24"},
  {title: "To Hell... And Back", episode_number: "S4, Ep25", description: "\nThe team head to Canada to investigate the disappearances of a number of homeless people, junkies and prostitutes and uncover something horrific.    ", season_id: 2489, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2009-05-20", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1422241/?ref_=ttep_ep25"},
  {title: "Doubt", episode_number: "S3, Ep1", description: "\nWhile a jury deliberates a case involving a co-ed accused of murder, ballistics expert Kurt McVeigh reenters Diane's life, while the awkwardness between Will and Alicia intensifies.    ", season_id: 2490, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2010-04-08", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1093934/?ref_=ttep_ep1"},
  {title: "In Name and Blood", episode_number: "S3, Ep2", description: "\nWith Gideon still missing, Hotchner puts in for a transfer and Prentiss tenders her resignation, but both are drawn back to work by a serial killer targeting women in a particularly heartless fashion.    ", season_id: 2490, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2007-10-03", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1111159/?ref_=ttep_ep2"},
  {title: "Scared to Death", episode_number: "S3, Ep3", description: "\nCastle is shaky after watching a DVD which predicts, in flashy amateur horror style, the exact time of death, for no apparent reason and probably by panic-caused cardiac arrest, of the murder victim, screaming in the phone, who received it. Her ex has a solid alibi and couldn't make sense of her panic about 'it'. Tracing the DVD's shipping leads to another copy recipient, killed at home similarly. Their only link is having been jurors on executed country serial killer Nigel Malloy's trial. The team heads for his home town, loved-ones and surviving jurors.    ", season_id: 2490, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2013-03-18", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1115047/?ref_=ttep_ep3"},
  {title: "Children of the Dark", episode_number: "S3, Ep4", description: "\nThe BAU travels to Denver, Colorado, where they investigate a series of home invasions that end in the murders of entire families. However, the case takes a turn when they begin to suspect that the killers were once-abused children.    ", season_id: 2490, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2007-10-17", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1110970/?ref_=ttep_ep4"},
  {title: "Seven Seconds", episode_number: "S3, Ep5", description: "\nThe unit works against the clock when a little girl disappears in a mall, believing a serial killer has struck a second time and the first girl died within an hour of abduction.    ", season_id: 2490, series_id: 27, season_episode_number: nil, air_date: "2007-10-24", seasonno: nil, url: "/title/tt1103432/?ref_=ttep_ep5"},
